<br>
When I was young I had a problem.  I had a big mouth.  My father warned me that &quot;the world&quot; would help me &quot;straighten that problem out&quot;.  True to his words one day I opened my mouth with the wrong intentions near the wrong person and I promptly got the snot kicked out of me.<br>
<br>
That was what it took for me to finally realize the utter necessity and correctness of what my father used to always say: <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> &quot;Think before you speak.&quot;</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Be wise and learn from my mistake instead of repeating it for yourself.<br>
<br>
Rather than blather about things that you have limited or no  knowledge of it is usually better to listen and/or ask questions instead of make statements.  If you choose to make statements without researching a topic or having a full understanding of the subject more often than not you will come across as unintelligent at best, ignorant at worst.  Even if you have been taught something in the past look at it again.  How current are you on the subject?  How real and unbiased was the information you received?  How much knowledge do you actually have on the subject as it relates to the &quot;big picture&quot;?<br>
<br>
Ignorance is the personal inablity to gain the knowledge that you are lacking in knowledge.  It is not realizing that you don't know something and being content with that.<br>
<br>
For other people to give your statements credibility you must come across to them as knowing what you are doing.  The reader must be able to trust the information you are giving them. If you bullshit them even once you lose a large portion of your credibility.  Disinformation and alarmism are the weapons of the mentally weak.<br>
<br>
If you want people to weigh your opinion on something then make sure you state it as opinion or concern and not as fact or &quot;common knowledge&quot;.<br>
<br>
If you are blissful in your ignorance more power to you - we leave you to it.  For the rest of our benefit please go sit in the corner and be quiet - the adults are talking. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ugenobi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>genobi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Junior Member</span><br>  Posts: 96<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/17/01 12:34:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=430.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> pre·ten·tious</span><hr size=1> I WAS TRYING TO CRAM BOTH MY FISTS UP MY ADULT ANUS TODAY, BUT THE SECOND ONE JUST WOULDN'T FIT.  SO I JUST WOUND UP PISSING MYSELF AND CRAMMING A PHILOSOPHICAL CAT UP MY ASS.  <br>
